    "name": "Nature (4)",
    "profile": "American rapper & songwriter from Queensbridge, New York (born December 5, 1973).\r\n[a=Nas] introduced Nature to the public in 1997, as a member of his supergroup [a=The Firm (6)], whose members also included [a=AZ] and [a=Foxy Brown]. Nature was brought in to replace rapper [a=Cormega], who had a contractual dispute with Nas' manager Steve Stoute. The Firm's first and only album, Nas, Foxy Brown, AZ, and Nature Present The Firm: The Album, went platinum, and topped the Billboard 200 album chart. The group disbanded in 1997 to pursue various solo projects. In 1998, Nature was featured on Noreaga's single \"Banned from T.V.\", alongside Big Pun, Cam'ron, Jadakiss and Styles P. After several delays, Nature's debut album For All Seasons, was released in 2000 by Columbia Records and featured a guest appearance from Nas. It reached number 50 on the Billboard 200. He followed this in 2002 with Wild Gremlinz, released on independent Sequence Records, which reached number 150 on the Billboard 200",
